Currently the content of MGCB files is unsorted.  The content files appear in the file as they exist in memory.  New stuff is added at the end and the order from opening an existing file is preserved.

This seemed like a good idea when I first wrote the code, but it completely stinks for merging .mgcb files or when working with multiple people.

If we do a simple sort in `PipelineProjectParser.SaveProject`:
```
// Sort the items alphabetically to ensure a consistent output
// and better mergability of the resulting MGCB file.
var sortedItems = _project.ContentItems.OrderBy(c => c.OriginalPath, StringComparer.InvariantCulture);

foreach (var i in sortedItems)
{
```

This works at the content is always in a consistent order when saving, it reduces merge conflicts, and makes it easier to compare changes.

The bad part in the code above is that a simple `OrderBy` string sort for a file path produces weird results.  There is a .NET Fiddle example here:   https://dotnetfiddle.net/Odactj

If someone can come up with a good sort this would make for a great PR.

The video player starts then stops then restarts fine.
